UNIX like system allows newlines in a file name. - <<beginning Portable Shell Scripts>> by Peter Seebach, Apress, 2008.
cat > "my filename with
newlines" <<EOF;
> Here we go - this this the contents of the file that has newline in its name.
> EOF
cat my filename with?newlines
Here we go - this this the contents of the file that has newline in its name.
